The paper also mentions the use of background theories with decidable satisfiability problems, which suggests a connection to logic and computation (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper's focus on decision procedures and SMT solvers suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper's use of quantified reasoning and logical fragments suggests a connection to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
